Kim Yong Nam Meets President of S. Korean Red Cross 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 1 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, met and conversed with Han Wan Sang, president of the south Korean Red Cross, and his party at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Thursday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Jang Jae On, chairman of the Central Committee of the DPRK Red Cross Society, and officials concerned.

Officials of Relevant Field Talk with Those Concerned of Hyundai Group 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 1 (KCNA) -- Officials of the relevant field in the DPRK talked with those concerned of Hyundai Group of south Korea at the People's Palace of Culture Thursday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there from the north side were officials of the relevant field including the National Economic Cooperation Federation and the National Reconciliation Council and from the south side those concerned of Hyundai Group including its Chairwoman Hyon Jong Un. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Both sides had general and inter-sector discussions on the cooperation in the work in the Kaesong Industrial Zone, tourism and social and cultural work and other issues of mutual concern. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Earlier, the chairwoman and her party toured the area of Mt. Paektu.

Greetings to Prime Minister of Antigua and Barbuda 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 1 (KCNA) -- Premier of the DPRK Cabinet Kim Yong Il sent a message of greetings to Baldwin Spencer, Prime Minister of Antigua and Barbuda, on the occasion of the 26th anniversary of its independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message wished the prime minister success in his work for the country's development and people's well-being.

18th National Program Contest and Exhibition Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 1 (KCNA) -- The 18th national program contest and exhibition were held in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Entries into the contest and exhibition which opened on October 24 included programs developed by ministries, national institutions and such fields as science, education, culture and public health. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The events were divided into the field of computerizing institutions, an exhibition of programs and contest. There was a contest in English-Korean translation programs. On display at the exhibition were hundreds of programs including scientific and technological calculation programs, business programs, designing programs and educational aid programs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A closing ceremony was held at the Three-Revolution Exhibition on October 31. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the ceremony were Ro Tu Chol, vice-premier of the Cabinet, Ri Kwang Ho, department director of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Pyon Yong Rip, president of the State Academy of Sciences, and other officials concerned, scientists, technicians and youths and students.

Sports Games of Artistes Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 1 (KCNA) -- The 38th sports games of artistes was held at Kim Il Sung Stadium on October 31. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They competed in football, basketball, volleyball, tug-of-war and other events, divided into groups of cinema, stage, education and production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the players fully displayed sports technique, high collectivist spirit and noble moral traits which they had cultivated through mass sports activities while engaging in energetic creative work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 The cheerers of all groups enthusiastically encouraged the players, presenting dances, band music, acrobatic feats, etc. and breaking into thunders of applause and cheers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The cinematic group took first place in total points.

Scenic Spots Change into New Looks 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 1 (KCNA) -- Scenic spots of the DPRK are being rebuilt as pleasure-grounds for the cultural rest of the working people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Ryongaksan Pleasure-Ground in Pyongyang and Mt. Paekun, a scenic spot, in South Hamgyong Province have been arranged more beautifully this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A road from the Mangyongdae Children's Camp to Tae Peak, top of Mt. Ryongak, many animal sculptures, resting sites and public service facilities were built in harmony in different parts of the pleasure-ground. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The camping houses were renovated and nearly 20 km-long trip road was expanded in the scenic spot. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A restaurant, parking lot, folklore amusement place are to be built in Sokam beauty spot of South Phyongan Province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 People in South Hwanghae Province are giving a finishing touch to the project for arranging Mt. Kuwol and Mt. Jangsu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Roads in Mt. Kuwol were expanded and resting sites and cultural welfare facilities were newly built to provide convenience to tourists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A loop tourist road linking Ju Peak and beautiful spots in Jaeryong County with the existing road is being formed and a pleasure-ground is being built well in Mt. Jangsu.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Projects for building scenic spots in various parts of the country including Mt. Myohyang, Ryongmun Cavern, Songam Cavern, Ulrim Falls, Mt. Chilbo and Chongsokjong more beautifully to suit the Songun era are being pushed ahead with redoubled efforts.

Teacher-Scholars Conducive to Scientific and Technological Development 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 1 (KCNA) -- Teacher-scholars in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea are taking a big share in developing rapidly the science and technology of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 High is the patriotic enthusiasm of university teachers to contribute to the building of a great, prosperous and powerful socialist country with great scientific research successes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In last 2-3 years alone they have settled one thousand and hundreds of important scientific and technological problems arising in such key basic IT, nano, bioengineering technologies and propelling the country's economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year teacher-scholars of Kim Il Sung University have made a new fodder additive for chicken with natural minerals abundant in the country instead of the imported fodder additive which had been used in the chicken farms and registered many research achievements. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those of Kim Chaek University of Technology have gone to industrial establishments, collieries, mines and construction sites in various parts of the country where projects for the technical modernization of the national economy are vigorously progressing apace. They are fully discharging their mission and duty as the pioneer of the IT industrial revolution while solving knotty scientific and technical problems on the site. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Han Tok Su Pyongyang University of Light Industry has made over a hundred research successes important for developing the light industry and introduced them into production. And Huichon University of Communications has conducted vigorously the collective scientific research activities to boost the communication science up to the level of cutting edge, thus advancing 700-odd inventions over the last three years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The scientific research successes of the teacher-scholars are a brilliant fruition born by the idea of the Workers' Party of Korea on attaching great importance to science, technology and education and on combining education with science and science with production.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Work Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 1 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Thursday dedicates a signed article to the 13th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's famous work "Socialism Is a Science." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work, published on Nov. 1, Juche 83 (1994), is an immortal library of weighty significance as it comprehensively deals with and systematizes the theory of socialism as a science, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More than a decade has passed since the publication of the work but Kim Jong Il's ideas and theories proving scientific accuracy of socialism and indicating a true path of its victory have displayed tremendous vitality with the lapse of time and the advance of the era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work, first of all, serves as an ideological pabulum as it instills unshakable faith in socialism into the people of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It comprehensively deals with the undisputed superiority of socialism to capitalism, the limitation of the preceding theory of socialism, originality and scientific accuracy of Juche-based theory of socialism, the deviations committed by some countries in building socialism in the past, the secret of the triumphant advance made by Korean-style socialism and the true advantages of Korean-style socialism centred on the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It, at the same time, serves as powerful guidelines for the building of a great prosperous powerful nation as it helps give full play to the advantages of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It clarifies important principled issues to be adhered to in socialist construction and the ways to do so. These issues include the issue of thoroughly embodying the principle of collectivism in all domains of social life, the issue of strengthening the driving force for the revolution and enhancing its role by giving priority to the ideological work and the work of remolding people, the issue of steadily improving the standard of the people's living as required by socialism by channeling great efforts into economic construction, the issue of building the Workers' Party of Korea as a mother party and pursuing the policy based on love, confidence and benevolence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work also serves as a banner encouraging the world revolutionary people in their advance toward independence and socialism.

